138.1	Accessibility	Accessibility	Accessibility is a general term used to describe the degree to which a product, device, service, or environment is available to as many people as possible. Accessibility can be viewed as the "ability to access" and benefit from some system or entity. Accessibility is often used to focus on people with disabilities or special needs and their right of access to entities, often through use of assistive technology.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Curitiba_10_2006_05_RIT.jpg/200px-Curitiba_10_2006_05_RIT.jpg
